{ { [%ai Black's structure is compromised.] } 11. Qxg4
{ [Source] as you can see the black King is completely unguarded doesn't matter which side he castles on it's going to be very hard for him to stay protected at the same time white has a very good defense he has three pawns three pawns he can Castle on the king side or the queen side { [%ai White wins a piece and maintains a dominant position.] }
) ( 8... Nh5 9. Qf3
{ [Source] Bobby Fischer recommended Queen to F3, which places significant pressure on the weak f7 square early in the opening. { [%ai A strong and thematic attacking move in the Fischer variation of the Sicilian.] }
9... d5
{ [Source] he can do this by one of two ways he can bring his Pawn to D5 or he can bring his Pawn to E6 { [%ai A direct challenge in the center, though it leads to sharp tactical themes.] }
( 9... e6
{ [Source] If instead if he plays E6 now we can bring our pawn and start to attack his Knight on H5 and again there's really only one move he can play now he can't bring it to F6 because we'll take it with our Pawn he's going to bring it back to G7 { [%ai Black chooses a defensive setup that blocks the white bishop but allows white to gain space and tempo by attacking the knight on the edge.] }
10. g4
{ { [%ai A thematic expansion to harass the knight, exploiting the lack of squares.] }
10... Ng7
{ [Source] he's going to bring it back to G7 as you can already see this is a very passive move he really wants to bring his dark Square Bishop to G7 and get it active attacking the dark squares along this long diagonal attacking the center but his dark Square Bishop is very passive now { [%ai The retreat to g7 is passive and obstructs the development of the f8-bishop, which is black's most important minor piece in this structure.] }
11. Ne4
{ [Source] from here we can continue and bring our Knight to E4 and this has a lot of problems for black there's not much can do here again we're attacking this Pawn on D6 we're also attacking this Square on F6 that would check the king he would be forced to move he couldn't take with his Queen because of our Pawn here { [%ai A strong centralizing move that eyes key weak squares in black's camp, specifically d6 and f6.] }
11... Qa5+
